Three persons were yesterday confirmed killed in a Thursday night attack by gunmen in Dong village, Bassa LGA of Plateau State. Residents of Miango Junction in Jos, less than three kilometres to Dong, had taken to social media Thursday night to report hearing gunshots despite a 6pm-6am curfew imposed on the by the state government. Police spokesman, ASP Tyopev Terna, told Daily Trust that three people were killed in the attack, even as more security agents had been deployed to the area. Governor Simon Lalong in a statement appealed for calm while sympathizing with the bereaved and assured them that government was taking steps to alleviate their pains.